1
00:00:06,972 --> 00:00:17,839
Uri Castle, picture plus card beauty spot in the hills of North Wales, became the focus of world sportsmen when Bruce Woodcock set up his training camp there to prepare for his World Heavyweight Championship fight with Lee Savold.

2
00:00:18,661 --> 00:00:28,268
Nu har 18 månader av förväntan, förvaltning och förväntan gått igen, och Jack Solomons, som är bakom allt, räddar sig med pressböjorna.

3
00:00:28,568 --> 00:00:29,189
Men bara lite.

4
00:00:29,728 --> 00:00:35,112
Med en man i Wales och en annan i Skarborough, Jack kanske måste röra från en kamp till en annan vid en viss anledning.

5
00:00:35,493 --> 00:00:37,996
Det är kriget av åldern för brittiska fans.

6
00:00:38,015 --> 00:00:43,500
Om Bruce vinner blir han världens första brittiska heavyweight-kämpare sen Cornishman Bob Fitzsimmons.

7
00:00:44,039 --> 00:00:48,506
En last minute hitch, en accident, kan rädda över natt månader av kostnadsförberedande.

8
00:00:48,966 --> 00:00:52,030
Men den här gången ser det aldrig ut som om alla signaler är klara.

9
00:01:08,347 --> 00:01:14,989
But if Jack Solomons was still worrying, Bruce didn't seem to have a care in the world as he dallied over tea with his hosts Leslie and Mrs. Saltz.

10
00:01:15,510 --> 00:01:20,650
Bruce owes a lot to Mr. Saltz, who did everything possible to give him the finest training camp in Britain.

11
00:01:20,751 --> 00:01:22,430
And Bruce has taken every advantage.

12
00:01:22,450 --> 00:01:25,852
Those who know him say he's never been so ready for a fight.

13
00:01:26,512 --> 00:01:32,612
More than any other, he's out to win this fight, if only to convince the nigglers who didn't like his win on a foul 18 months ago.

14
00:01:35,334 --> 00:01:36,614
And now, the White City.

15
00:01:37,259 --> 00:01:42,444
A record, excited crowd, searing floodlights and all that makes a Solomons night of nights.

16
00:01:43,084 --> 00:01:45,266
It's a fantastic scene in the vast arena.

17
00:01:46,548 --> 00:01:55,996
Ringside seats within handshake reach of the fighters and far in the distance the real fans perched high and looking hopefully at a shining pocket handkerchief with two fleas hopping on it.

18
00:01:56,658 --> 00:02:01,763
Fight reporter Desmond Hackett punches out pre-fight impressions and is all set to report the big fight for you.

19
00:02:04,170 --> 00:02:08,811
Bretons highly successful film producer Sir Michael Bolton chats with a smiling Jack Solomons.

20
00:02:08,830 --> 00:02:09,871
No wonder he's smiling.

21
00:02:11,711 --> 00:02:15,331
There is Sir Arthur Elvin and GRA boss Frank Gentle.

22
00:02:16,192 --> 00:02:22,473
The preliminaries are over and excitement soars as the moment draws near for the fighters to enter the ring.

23
00:02:22,493 --> 00:02:33,855
The spotlight picks up the stars and stripes as Lee Savold of America and his escort march into the arena.

24
00:02:51,939 --> 00:02:53,700
Och nu en rådgivning för Britanniens Bruce Woodcock som visade oss hans väg genom staden.

25
00:03:27,021 --> 00:03:30,632
Freddy Mils är där och brusar bruskligt mellan väggarna.

26
00:03:30,651 --> 00:03:32,837
Det är ingen av de gamla kvaliteterna den här tiden.

27
00:03:39,556 --> 00:03:40,257
Patsy Higgins.

28
00:03:40,317 --> 00:03:41,098
En tjej i spetmöten.

29
00:04:09,705 --> 00:04:11,026
And there they are, ready to decide who is the world's best.

30
00:04:11,046 --> 00:04:11,586
It's seconds out and time.

31
00:04:11,606 --> 00:04:12,288
Who's going to make the first move?

32
00:04:12,307 --> 00:04:12,807
It may be the first slip.

33
00:04:12,828 --> 00:04:14,909
Many experts thought it would be Savold, out to catch Bruce with a confidence wrecker before he got set.

34
00:04:36,661 --> 00:04:39,843
Those who tipped a Woodcock win banked on his hair-trigger right.

35
00:04:39,862 --> 00:04:42,906
But all agreed they'd be throwing punches from the word go.

36
00:04:58,877 --> 00:05:03,060
New York fight experts Nat Fleischer and Lou Burstyn wonder if the title is going to cross the Atlantic.

37
00:05:09,867 --> 00:05:11,528
Det var rätt, tre round rapid.

38
00:05:11,548 --> 00:05:14,451
Det var inga powderpuff-puncher, de skickade nog Savold.

39
00:05:19,634 --> 00:05:22,997
Ända av round one, och Woodcock går till en flygande start.

40
00:05:25,180 --> 00:05:30,244
Round two, med vänstern jabbade hela tiden på Savold, och rätt kom över när det skulle göra mest skador.

41
00:05:30,504 --> 00:05:32,206
Bruce tog round two hansomt.

42
00:05:48,899 --> 00:05:48,980
Tack!

43
00:06:19,153 --> 00:06:23,297
Här uppe i staden, kapten Ayers och medlemmar av hans Storbritanniska staff, håll kvar.

44
00:06:28,701 --> 00:06:29,062
Rund tre.

45
00:06:53,932 --> 00:06:57,158
Woodcock still throwing that shattering right, but he's not cashing in.

46
00:06:57,177 --> 00:06:58,259
He's not following up.

47
00:06:58,581 --> 00:06:59,641
He gives Savold a breather.

48
00:06:59,802 --> 00:07:02,947
That one good breath is all that tough campaigner needs to get out of trouble.

49
00:07:26,509 --> 00:07:29,411
Det var en överraskande paket, men inget stoppade Savold från att komma in och fråga om det.

50
00:07:29,432 --> 00:07:33,336
Vid slutet av tredje rounden såg de sig oroliga i Savolds klocka.

51
00:07:33,355 --> 00:07:33,795
Lees är långt bakom.

52
00:07:33,836 --> 00:07:35,918
De första tre rounderna är brusar.

53
00:07:35,958 --> 00:07:37,338
Och nu den dramatiska fjärde rounden.

54
00:08:11,749 --> 00:08:12,350
There it is!

55
00:08:12,370 --> 00:08:14,031
The punch that cut Bruce's eye.

56
00:08:14,050 --> 00:08:18,954
It was the payoff punch, though we didn't know it at first till we saw blood streaming down his face and blinding him.

57
00:08:19,394 --> 00:08:22,577
For the first time, Woodcock became a real fighting fury.

58
00:08:22,598 --> 00:08:24,059
For him it was a quick KO win or the end.

59
00:08:25,470 --> 00:08:29,141
Savold to knew that this was his chance and moved in savagely for the kill.

60
00:08:29,182 --> 00:08:30,786
There's too much at stake for sentiment.

61
00:09:21,244 --> 00:09:22,325
Så är det bra.

62
00:09:22,384 --> 00:09:24,785
Dramatisk, unexpected change.

63
00:09:25,293 --> 00:09:28,274
Till Ringsiders var det tydligt att Bruce var för hård att kämpa på.

64
00:09:28,293 --> 00:09:46,201
Ta en titt på det där ögonen.

65
00:09:46,221 --> 00:09:52,384
Det borde skada de som skrattade och trodde att Woodcock hade avslutat när Tom Hurst kallade det för en dag för att rädda Bruce från en mörk målning.

66
00:09:54,065 --> 00:09:54,785
Det är ett och ett nu.

67
00:09:54,806 --> 00:09:56,307
Låt oss hoppas att Bruce öppnar snabbt och bra.

68
00:09:56,327 --> 00:09:57,429
För att ge honom en chans för beslutaren.

69
00:09:57,450 --> 00:09:58,571
Som för Lee har han gjort många vänner här.

70
00:09:58,591 --> 00:09:59,052
I dag är det hans dag.

71
00:09:59,072 --> 00:09:59,552
I dag är han Lee Savold.

72
00:09:59,572 --> 00:10:00,193
Hjärnvägskampion i världen.
